description: Altrincham end their seven-game winless in the National League by edging past Yeovil.
title: Altrincham 2-1 Yeovil Town
title_page: National League: Altrincham 2-1 Yeovil Town - BBC Sport
maintext:
Altrincham ended their run of seven games without a win in the National League with victory at home to Yeovil.
The Robins took the lead on the half-hour mark when Tylor Golden got on the end of Tom Crawford's cross to convert at the back post.
The home side's lead lasted just two minutes, however, as Frankie Terry poked the ball past Caleb Ansen to equalise for Yeovil.
Regan Linney twice came close for Altrincham after the break before Lewis Baines scored with two minutes remaining to secure the three points.
